<p>I have a list of <code>tags</code> I want to display horizontally. Now for each <code>&lt;li&gt;</code>, but the last one, I want to add a <code>,</code> after the item.</p>  <p>Now, I can do that of course:</p>  <pre><code>ul.tags {     list-style: none; }  ul.tags &gt; li {     display: inline; }  ul.tags &gt; li:after {     content: ", "; }  ul.tags &gt; li:last-of-type:after {     content: ""; } </code></pre>  <p>Now I thought about combining the last two rules, like:</p>  <pre><code>ul.tags &gt; li:not(ul.tags &gt; li:last-of-type):after {     content: ", "; } </code></pre>  <p>But this does not work. How can I select all <b>but the last</b> <code>&lt;li&gt;</code>?</p>